<br>
I am certain most of you may have heard of us, and many may have had bad impressions. I know quite a few of your allied members, so they can vouch for my honesty, if not my creed.<br>
<br>
As many of the higher leveled nightmare clanians can no longer hunt the dragons nag and vox, the level 52 members and 53 members are looking to see if you would like our added assistance into taking down these dragons.<br>
<br>
If not we can form other alliances, hopefully so that our members get to kill their dragons which many of them haven't done often.<br>
<br>
To this I leave in your hands, if you would like to ally with the lower lvl members of our guild for these type of hunts, we would, I am assuming happily accept.<br>
<br>
Cheers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(10/19/00 8:28:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nightmare Clan  wishes to participate</span><hr size=1> Tigerlight,<br>
<br>
The organizer of the Dragon raid is going to be the person who decides who goes on the raid and doesn't. Right now, Jzonn is our man in that role, so he'll make the call. <br>
<br>
The CoG Dragon raids are set up in principle so that anyone can attend, at the discretion of the raid organizer. Their main focus is to provide access to a dragon raid for those guilds who cannot otherwise attend a dragon raid. This could apply equally well to those guilds whose members have grown higher in levels than is allowed to fight Vox or Nagafen. <br>
<br>
Sign up in the proper thread in this forum and if you can make it, I'm sure Jzonn wouldn't mind having you.<br>
<br>
Haemish MacLennan<br>
Clan Chieftan<br>
The Silver Daggers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujzonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jzonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(10/19/00 8:29:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> You might want to consider...</span><hr size=1> ...hosting your own spot on the raid for the CoG.  You'll need to abide by the CoG rules regarding participants and loot distribution.  It will give more members of the Karana community a chance at the dragons and provide a fresh approach to the process of executing a large scale raid. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utigerlight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tigerlight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(10/23/00 7:03:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.haleohana.com/members/images/tigerlight.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: You might want to consider...</span><hr size=1> I don't entirely understand that. But if what you mean is that NC sponsors a spot on the rotation then I will place one up. The fact that is that my guild does not mind to adhere to the rules of CoG and would also be more than pleased to participate to help those other guilds who normally could not do the dragons.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(10/23/00 8:28:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: You might want to consider...</span><hr size=1> What Jzonn means is that you do what he has done for the Council. You get a spot for Nightmare Clan on the Dragon rotation, and bill it as a NC/CoG spot on the rotation, i.e. invite any members of the Council to attend via sign up on this board. If NC has say 10-15 spots that they can regularly fill, but that isn't enough to take down the dragon (not sure on numbers here), schedule a spot, and when you are up, invite CoG members on this board to sign up. <br>
<br>
It's an organizational nightmare (no pun intended), I'm sure, but if you are willing to do it, and abide by the normal CoG rules, (exclude no one, regardless of guild or non-guild, loot by lotto with NO priority given to anyone on loot, only lotto among those classes present who can use the item, etc.), then the CoG is behind you on it. <br>
<br>
Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showPrevMessage?topicID=19.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showNextMessage?topicID=19.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.emailToFriend?topicID=19.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.threadControl?topicID=19.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=19.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=19.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub6.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="councilofguildsgeneral">General<option value="councilofguildscouncildiscussions">Council Discussions<option value="councilofguildsevents">Events<option value="councilofguildscogplanesraidschedule">CoG Planes Raid Schedule<option value="councilofguildsfrm8">CoG Dragon Raids<opt